update public.lessons l set enhancements = $ench${"industryStory":"A graduate of this kind of programme walked into interviews with a public portfolio, a tailored CV and rehearsed STAR stories. They were not the most experienced candidate — but they were the most prepared and credible, and that won the role.","davidTip":"Be systematic about the search: track applications, follow up politely, and tailor each one. Most candidates do not follow up — doing so sets you apart. And keep your portfolio and CV current as you learn.","miniChallenge":"Draft your final QA career action plan: target roles, where you will apply, how you will track applications, and your next skill to build.","modelAnswer":"## Example\nTarget: junior QA / QA analyst roles. Apply via LinkedIn + 3 job boards, tracked in a simple sheet (company, role, date, status, next action). Follow up 3–5 days after applying. Next skill: deepen automation basics. Portfolio + CV kept current.","managersReview":{"intro":"If I assessed your final project and job-readiness as a hiring manager, I would look for:","strengths":["A complete, public portfolio","Tailored CV/LinkedIn linked to it","Rehearsed, structured interview answers","A clear, organised job-search plan"],"gaps":["Portfolio incomplete or private","Generic applications","Unstructured interview answers"],"improvements":["Finish and publish every artefact","Tailor each application","Rehearse STAR answers out loud"]},"portfolioBuilder":"This is the finish line: a complete QA portfolio, a tailored CV and LinkedIn, rehearsed interview answers and a job-search plan. You are now genuinely job-ready — present your work with confidence.","resourcePreview":{"name":"Final Portfolio Project Workbook","purpose":"Pulls your course work into a complete, job-winning portfolio and action plan.","whenToUse":"Use it to finalise your portfolio and graduation submission.","formats":["DOCX","PDF"]}}$ench$::jsonb
